## 3. System Usage Guide

### 3.1 Dashboard & KPIs
The landing page provides academic performance indicators:
- **Total Students, Streams, and Courses** active in the system.
- **Pass Rate & Mean Score:** Dynamically computed from all gradebook entries.
- **Stream Performance Chart:** Compares class averages to identify streams requiring attention.
- **Academic Leaderboard:** Lists top-performing students across the academy.

### 3.2 Managing Class Streams
Navigate to **Class Streams** to:
- Add new class streams (e.g., "Grade 10-A", "Grade 10-B").
- Assign physical room numbers and class teachers.
- View class-specific rosters and room details.

### 3.3 Student Directory
Navigate to **Student Folder** to:
- Register new students. Admission numbers are automatically generated (`IXA-YYYY-XXX`).
- Update student profiles (DOB, Gender, Parent/Guardian contact details).
- Change status (Active, Suspended, Transferred).
- Access individual **Report Cards** with detailed subject breakdowns, class position rankings, and a PDF download feature.

### 3.4 Curriculum Management
Navigate to **Curriculum** to:
- Manage subjects, course codes, and departments.
- Assign subjects to specific Class Streams to populate their study schedules.

### 3.5 Gradebook (Scoring Grid)
Navigate to **Scoring Grid** to input student assessment marks:
- Select a **Stream** and a **Subject**.
- Input **Continuous Assessment (CA)** (out of 30) and **Exam** marks (out of 70).
- System validates score ranges in real-time.
- Click **Save Grades** to persist records to the database.

### 3.6 Rankings Engine & Grade Boundaries
Navigate to **Rankings Engine** to:
- Define grading bands (A, B, C, D, F) with customizable point boundaries and remarks.
- Click **Update Grading Criteria** to save. This automatically triggers a recalculation of all grades in the database.
- Recalculate stream-wise positions using a dense ranking algorithm based on student term averages.
